<P>
NATION IN BRIEF; FLORIDA; ASTRONAUTS LOCATE MISSING MOSQUITO 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Great Mosquito Hunt aboard space shuttle Endeavour is over. The insect was 
sucked into the filter of a fan and squashed, astronauts reported to the 
Kennedy Space Center.They had been looking for the intruder since first 
spotting it after they arrived in orbit Friday. The insect interlude did not 
interfere with the mission of the shuttle's powerful radar system to examine 
the Earth's surface. The radar scanned more volcanoes, including Sicily's Mt. 
Etna and Hawaii's Kilauea. 
</P>
