</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Fountain Valley defeated a team representing Southern states to win the U.S. 
Tennis Assn. women's team title Sunday at Nevada Las Vegas. 
</P>
<P>
 Fountain Valley, representing Southern California, defeated Southern, 2-1. 
</P>
<P>
 The Fountain Valley men's team lost the title match to Texas, 2-1. Dexter 
MacBride and former UC Irvine player Bruce Man Son Hing defeated Colin Hiu and 
Larry Pascal, 6-3, 6-4. Fountain Valley's No. 1 doubles team of Kent Seton and 
Doug Iesenman had match point in a tiebreaker in the third set but lost to 
Mitch Michulan and Johan Svensson, 5-7, 7-6 (7-5), 7-6 (8-6). 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 The U.S. Tennis Assn. national seniors hardcourt championships in the women's 
65 and 75 divisions begin today and continue through Saturday at the Newport 
Beach Tennis Club. 
</P>
<P>
 Doris Clark of Laguna Beach is top-seeded in the 65 singles, followed by 
Louise Owen of Evansville, Ind. Dodo Cheney of Santa Monica is seeded first in 
the 75s with Alice Beckenbach of Los Angeles second. 
</P>
<P>
 Louise Harper of La Jolla and Owen are top-seeded in the 65 doubles. Cheney 
and Pat Stuhler of Brielle, N.J., are seeded first in the 75 doubles. 
</P>
<P>
 Play begins at 10:30 a.m. today. The Marriott Hotel Tennis Club at Fashion 
Island will be the secondary site for some of the early matches. Semifinals 
will be played Friday, with the finals Saturday beginning at 9:30 a.m. 
</P>
