<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 During the housing boom of the 1960s, county officials changed the names of 
many roads to make them consistent throughout the county. 
</P>
<P>
 Roads originally named after tiny towns and junctions -- such as Wintersburg, 
Smeltzer and Delhi -- were among those changed. The goal of the name changes 
was to make it easier for drivers to find their way around the county. Here are 
a few of the name changes: 02,31,22 Old name Current name Smeltzer Avenue 
Edinger Avenue Bay Boulevard Seal Beach Boulevard Stanton Avenue/ Beach 
Boulevard Huntington Beach Boulevard Wintersburg Avenue/Delhi Road Warner 
Avenue Verano Avenue Euclid Street Wright Street Brookhurst Street Cannery 
Street Magnolia Street  
</P>
