<HEADLINE>
<P>
DRIVING CLASSES COULD HELP SENIORS QUALIFY FOR DISCOUNTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Driving classes for senior citizens who want to improve their driving skills 
and qualify for insurance discounts will be held throughout South County this 
month. 
</P>
<P>
 Aimed at helping seniors adjust to deteriorating reflexes and vision, the 
course is held over two days at many sites in South County. 
</P>
<P>
 Called "55 Alive," the program is sponsored by the American Assn. of Retired 
Persons, and participants must be at least age 50. Registration costs $8, and 
preregistration is required. 
</P>
<P>
 Upon completing the two-day course, seniors receive a certificate that can be 
sent to auto insurance companies for good driver discounts. 
</P>
<P>
 Those interested in signing up must contact the facility where the class is 
being held. Here's where classes in South County will be held: 
</P>
<P>
 * Monday, Oct. 10, and Tuesday, Oct. 11, from 9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the San 
Clemente Community and Senior Citizen Center, 242 Avenida del Mar, in San 
Clemente. For more information, call (714) 498-3322. 
</P>
<P>
 * Monday, Oct. 10, and Tuesday, Oct. 11, from 8 a.m. to noon at the Norman P. 
Murray Community and Senior Center, 24932 Oso Viejo Road, in Mission Viejo. For 
more information, call (714) 348-2063. 
</P>
<P>
 * Wednesday, Oct. 19, and the following Wednesday, Oct. 26, from 9:30 a.m. to 
2 p.m. at the Capistrano Bay Park and Recreation District, 34052 Del Obispo 
St., in Dana Point. For more information, call (714) 496-4252. 
</P>
<P>
 * Thursday, Oct. 20, and Friday, Oct. 21, from 12:30 to 4:30 p.m. at the 
Freedom Village Retirement Community, 23442 El Toro Road, in Lake Forest. For 
more information, call (714) 472-4700. 
</P>
<P>
 * Thursday, Oct. 20, and Friday, Oct. 21, from 1 to 5 p.m. at the Glendale 
Federal Bank, 24221 Calle De La Louisa, in Laguna Hills. For more information, 
call (714) 768-7771. 
</P>
<P>
 * Thursday, Oct. 27, and Friday, Oct. 28, from 9:30 a.m. to 2 p.m. at the Sea 
Country Senior Community Center, 24602 Aliso Creek Road, in Laguna Niguel. For 
more information, call (714) 362-4342. FRANK MESSINA 
</P>
</TEXT>
