SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: ORANGE COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Carl's Jr./Green Burrito to Open: The Orange County-based Carl's Jr. and Green 
Burrito fast-food restaurant chains will open their first joint eatery 
Wednesday in a Carl's Jr. restaurant at 21704 S. Avalon in Carson.The store is 
one of six being converted to sell both Carl's Jr. hamburgers and Green 
Burrito's Mexican-style food. Executives at Anaheim-based Carl's Jr. said the 
experiment will be considered a success if the combined menus bolster overall 
revenue without siphoning off existing sales. Several regional fast-food 
companies, including Long John Silver's and Arby's, are experimenting with 
serving two brands of food under the same roof. The idea of putting Carl's Jr. 
and Green Burrito under a single roof was a pet project of Carl's founder Carl 
N. Karcher. He believed in the idea so strongly that it cost him the 
chairmanship. The board of directors voted to replace him last October after it 
initially refused to go along with the idea of testing Green Burrito operations 
in their restaurants. Karcher was later restored as chairman emeritus, and the 
company relented on the Green Burrito test idea in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
