PEOPLE: FIRST INTERSTATE BANK APPOINTS SENIOR VICE PRESIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 First Interstate Bank of California has appointed Richard Shuttleworth senior 
vice president in addition to his position as regional manager of Orange County 
corporate banking. Shuttleworth joined the Los Angeles-based bank in 1977 and 
was assigned to the Chicago representative office as a corporate lending 
officer in 1979. He served in the same capacity with the bank's metropolitan 
division in Los Angeles beginning in 1983 and with its international operations 
in Hong Kong in 1985, prior to being assigned to Orange County corporate 
banking in 1987 where he has been regional manager since 1989. 
</P>
