<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOUTHLAND PREVIEW / THE BUSINESS WEEK AHEAD: LOS ANGELES COUNTY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Furniture Makers Workshop: The Assn. of Woodworking and Furnishings Suppliers 
is leading a workshop today to explore water-based adhesives for furniture 
manufacturers as an alternative to the popular but environmentally harmful 
adhesives now in use.The conference, designed to help Southern California 
furniture makers comply with environmental regulations, is co-sponsored by the 
Institute for Research and Technical Assistance and various environmental 
groups. The Air Quality Management District has pressured furniture 
manufacturers to abandon the use of volatile organic compound-based adhesives, 
which contribute to smog levels, and to phase out the use of 
trichloroethane-based adhesives, which contribute to ozone depletion. The 
workshop will begin at 8:15 a.m. at the Southern California Edison Customer 
Technology Application Center in Irwindale. 
</P>
