<P>
 Judge Orders Procter & Gamble to Settle Suit: Halting a trial, a judge in 
Pittsburgh told the consumer products company to try to settle its suit against 
two former researchers who left to work for competitor Johnson & Johnson. The 
suit alleges that the researchers violated an agreement not to engage in 
similar work with a competitor for three years. The judge said he was 
disappointed that the two sides had not taken him seriously when he urged a 
settlement at pretrial meetings, and he threatened to revoke the Ohio courtroom 
privileges of three New Jersey lawyers representing Johnson & Johnson if a deal 
is not reached by this morning. 
