<TEXT>
<P>
 Surging Imports Widen Trade Deficit Down Under: Australia's trade deficit was 
wider in August than it's been in more than four years, a result of surging 
imports that signal the economy is growing fast enough to spur inflation, 
analysts said. The current account deficit expanded 18% to a seasonally 
adjusted $1.56 billion, from a revised $1.32 billion in July, the Australian 
Bureau of Statistics said. 
