<P>
 August Unemployment Remains at 3%: Japan's unemployment rate remained stuck at 
around 3% in August, although the number of people out of work edged up to 2 
million, according to the official Management and Coordination Agency. The 
August rate was 3.01%, or a seasonally adjusted 3%, up from 2.96% in July and 
2.5% in August last year. The jobless rate for July and August is the highest 
since June, 1987, when Japan's economy suffered a slump caused by the high yen. 
