<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOME OF COUNTY'S RICH GETTING EVEN RICHER, FORBES FINDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some of Orange County's richest people have gotten even richer. 
</P>
<P>
 According to the newly released annual Forbes 400 Richest People in America 
list, Donald Bren, the 62-year-old chairman of the Irvine Co., jumped from No. 
54 in 1993 to No. 35 this time, with a net worth of $2 billion.That's up from 
$1.3 billion last year. 
</P>
<P>
 Anne Catherine Getty Earhart, 42, of Laguna Beach has a rank of 189 with $550 
million to her name, up from $400 million last year. Her sister, Claire Eugenia 
Getty Perry, 40, listed as having moved from Laguna Beach to San Francisco, 
possesses the same amount of wealth, according to Forbes. 
</P>
<P>
 And Joan Irvine Smith, 61, of Corona del Mar, who previously was included in a 
section of Forbes magazine that listed wealthy families, is now listed as an 
individual. She is ranked 341 and her fortune weighed in at $350 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Forbes reports that Katsumasa (Roy) Sakioka, 96, is still worth $350 million, 
the same as in 1993. 
</P>
</TEXT>
