<HEADLINE>
<P>
FIRE DAMAGES HOUSE IN NEWPORT BEACH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Firefighters quickly extinguished an early morning fire that caused an 
estimated $50,000 damage Sunday in an East Bluff townhouse, a Fire Department 
spokesman said. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire broke out at 3:58 a.m. at the home of Richard Cooling and his wife in 
the 400 block of Vista Trucha. With 29 firefighters on the scene, the blaze was 
controlled in 25 minutes, and no injuries were reported. 
</P>
<P>
 The fire is believed to have started in a garage workshop, and most of the 
damage was confined to the garage. 
</P>
