<HEADLINE>
<P>
SAN JUAN CAPISTRANO PLANNERS OK 1ST PHASE OF SPORTS PARK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Planning Commission has approved the first phase of a $3.8-million city 
sports park. 
</P>
<P>
 The facility, which includes a community center, a swimming pool and fields 
for baseball, softball and soccer, will be built next to Marco Forster Middle 
School, near Camino del Avion and Del Obispo Street. 
</P>
<P>
 The project is being funded by a 1990 local bond measure. 
</P>
<P>
 Commissioners had only a few concerns last week when reviewing proposed zoning 
changes and other permits to allow construction of the ball fields, bleachers, 
snack bar, a roadway and parking lot. 
</P>
<P>
 Some said they were worried that the planned roadway through the sports park 
might be used as a shortcut by motorists. The roadway will have a speed limit 
of 25 m.p.h. 
</P>
<P>
 But city staff assured the commission that the road would be gently winding 
and not attractive as a shortcut for cars. 
</P>
<P>
 The roadway straddles a proposed site for an elementary school. 
</P>
<P>
 The sports park, when finished, will end a long wait by residents who approved 
bonds for the project. 
</P>
<P>
 Plans for the community center and swimming pool are to be considered later by 
the commission. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'd like to get moving on the project," said commission member Wyatt Hart. 
"It's been four years. It's been long enough." JEFF BEAN 
</P>
</TEXT>
