<HEADLINE>
<P>
COSTA MESA POLICE SEEK CLUES IN FATAL STABBING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A man found dead on a sidewalk Saturday night had been fatally stabbed, police 
said Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 The victim, a Latino adult who was not identified pending notification of his 
family, was found at 11 p.m. by a pedestrian walking near the intersection of 
Wallace Avenue and James Street in a residential area in the city's southwest, 
police Sgt. Rich Bell said. 
</P>
<P>
 No weapon was found, Bell said, and police know of no motive or witnesses. 
</P>
<P>
 Police have asked that any witnesses or anyone with any information call 
detectives at (714) 754-5205 or (714) 754-5255. 
</P>
