<HEADLINE>
<P>
MITSUBISHI ELECTRIC AMERICA TO MERGE 2 OF ITS DIVISIONS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mitsubishi Electric America said two of the company's affiliates will merge. 
</P>
<P>
 Mitsubishi Consumer Electronics America, with operations in Santa Ana and 
Braselton, Ga., will combine electronics manufacturing and marketing activities 
with Mitsubishi Electronics America.The new company will be based in Norcross, 
Ga., and will keep the Mitsubishi Consumer Electronics America name. It will 
handle audio-video products and cellular telephones. 
</P>
<P>
 MCEA will keep its current operations in Santa Ana, the company said Friday. 
</P>
<P>
 Mitsubishi Electronics' chairman, Takeo Iinuma, said the merger will take 
effect Jan. 1. The company's Consumer Electronics Group will combine its 
marketing and operations resources with MCEA's TV engineering and manufacturing 
facilities. 
</P>
<P>
 "This restructuring will provide a substantial means for increasing our 
profitability and competitiveness in the U.S. market," Iinuma said. 
</P>
<P>
 MELA and MCEA are two of 12 affiliated companies operating within the 
Mitsubishi Electric America group, which has 4,500 employees in more than 30 
locations and annual sales of nearly $3 billion. 
</P>
<P>
 Mitsubishi Electric America is a U.S. subsidiary of Japan's Mitsubishi Group, 
one of the world's largest diversified companies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
