<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; WOMAN'S CONDITION CRITICAL AFTER CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Ventura woman was in critical condition Sunday after suffering severe head 
injuries when her car careened off California 33 in front of the Villanova 
Preparatory School in Ojai, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Rosalie Elizabeth Rivas, 27, was driving southbound on California 33 about 
9:45 p.m. Saturday when she lost control of her vehicle and slammed through the 
rail outside the private school, Ventura County sheriff's deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 The car struck a tree just off the roadway, and the top portion of the vehicle 
was sheared off, causing severe head injuries to Rivas. 
</P>
<P>
 The car came to rest upside down on the front lawn of the campus, officials 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The single-car accident was discovered by a passerby who alerted officials. 
</P>
<P>
 Rivas was transported to Ojai Valley Hospital for immediate treatment, 
deputies said. 
</P>
<P>
 She was stabilized at the Ojai hospital and transferred to Ventura County 
Medical Center in Ventura, where hospital officials listed her condition Sunday 
as critical. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
