<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: OXNARD; MOTORCYCLIST KILLED IN CRASH IS IDENTIFIED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Authorities on Sunday identified the motorcyclist who was killed in a weekend 
head-on collision as Danny Lee Becker, 40, of Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 Becker was killed instantly Saturday along Pacific Coast Highway when he 
struck a car driven by Shannon Orick, 19, of Oxnard. 
</P>
<P>
 California Highway Patrol officials said Becker was driving north on the 
southbound lanes of the highway for unknown reasons when he hit Orick's car. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokesman at St. John's Regional Medical Center listed Orick's condition 
Sunday as serious. 
</P>
<P>
 Two passengers -- Elizabeth Espinoza, 19, and Xiomara Neadeau, 17, both of 
Oxnard -- were treated for injuries and released, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 CHP officials said Becker was driving north in the southbound lanes of the 
highway about 7:15 p.m. when he struck the vehicle driven by Orick head-on. 
Orick's car rolled over onto the northbound lanes and crashed through a 
chain-link fence before coming to rest. 
</P>
<P>
 The highway was closed for three hours Saturday night while investigators 
cleared the wreckage. 
</P>
<P>
 A Ventura County coroner's official said Becker was unemployed. He is survived 
by his parents, Vernon and Mary Becker of Oregon. 
</P>
<P>
 An autopsy was scheduled for today, Senior Deputy Coroner Mitch Breese said 
Sunday. JEFF McDONALD 
</P>
</TEXT>
