<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; REWARD OFFERED IN WOMAN'S MUGGING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 East Ventura County sheriff's detectives are offering a $1,000 reward for the 
identify of a man who mugged a Thousand Oaks woman Sept. 12 outside The Oaks 
mall. 
</P>
<P>
 The man is described as having blond hair and a tattoo around his right wrist 
that depicts barbed wire, and wearing a green plaid shirt and heavy boots.The 
woman was robbed as she got into her car at 12:45 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Authorities said he approached the woman from behind, told her he had a gun, 
and forced her to hand over $35,000 worth of jewelry. Sheriff's officials said 
they hope a passerby saw the crime or the suspect as he fled. 
</P>
<P>
 The reward is part of the Sheriff Department's Ventura County Crime Stoppers 
program. People who call with information can remain anonymous and if the 
information leads to an arrest with a criminal court complaint, the caller will 
receive the reward. 
</P>
<P>
 Crime Stoppers' phone number is 494-TALK in Moorpark and Thousand Oaks, 
987-TALK in Camarillo, 385-TALK in Oxnard and 986-TALK in Port Hueneme. MATTHEW 
MOSK 
</P>
